main event: A possible satellite sighting was reported on March 16, 1963 in the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The object was described as a 'space born object, small and circular, resembling bright star'.
The object was tracked through 30 degrees of arc from 192 degrees true to 132 degrees true.
The reporting aircraft's position was 36.32N 174.02W in the Pacific Ocean.
The object was reported to be at an unknown altitude, about 35 degrees above the horizon.
The report mentions details about the time, latitude, and longitude of the object's northbound and southbound positions.
sighted object: small, circular object resembling a bright star
